My recommended v2.2 punch list

If I were editing this into a near-final architecture doc, I would make these next:

Split orchestrator contract into embedded vs external subsections and update the diagrams.

Rewrite approval-pipeline reject paths to match strict fresh-container retries.

Resolve the implementation-vs-test-generation sequencing and define the post-test-failure loop.

Scope budget language to engine-managed spend in external client mode.

Replace “force to BitNet” with “force to local-only execution class.”

Normalize lock resources and add explicit eco_ref/task-lineage schema support.

Make CLI/API index queries fully typed and consistent.

Add explicit container hardening policy.

Treat warm sandbox pools as optional optimization with reset guarantees.

Remove the separate Claw SRS bypass knob and keep delegated approval only.

So the honest answer is: this is very good now. It reads like a serious system design instead of a smart concept note. The remaining issues are concrete enough that a v2.2 can probably settle most of them.
